VL_NOPREFIX() creats prefix-less stubs for VLFeat functions (e.g. SIFT for VL_SIFT). This function is seldom used as the stubs are included in the VLFeat binary distribution anyways. Moreover, on UNIX platforms, the stubs are generally constructed by the Makefile.

See also: VL_COMPILE(), VL_HELP().
